hing, pureand simple, beyondour own complexities.\n\n- William\n|\nHe who knows all the answers, but none of the questions is like a large gobbling bird on Thanksgiving.\n\n- Jayce\n|\nAll paths are present, always... and we can but choose among them.\n\n- Jacqueline Carey, Kushiel's Chosen\n|\nWhen you live in darkness, you live under the rulership of the devil.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nPeople who know God truly change the life of their nation, and not the government\n\n- Sunday\n|\nI may not have a degree, but I certainly got an education.\n\n- Jodi Picoult, Lone Wolf\n|\nIf you can begin with enthusiasm and confidence, you are half way to success.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nInevitably, if we are to grow and change as adults, we must gradually learn to confront the challenges, paradoxes, problems and painful reality of an insecure world.\n\n- James P. Krehbiel, Stepping Out of the Bubble: Reflections on the Pilgrimage of Counseling Therapy\n|\nWe all have the Wisdom to understand that sooner or later Life will end, but we don’t have the Willpower to Live before we die.\n\n- RVM\n|\nWater, water, everywhere,And all the boards did shrink;Water, water, everywhere,Nor any drop to drink.\n\n- Samuel Taylor Coleridge, The Rime of the Ancient Mariner\n|\nI answer the heroic question, 'Death, where is thy sting?' with 'It is in my heart and mind and memories.\n\n- Maya\n|\nThe aim of art is to represent not the outward appearance of things, but their inward significance.\n\n- Aristotle\n|\nSo many wish for magic so many beg for fame, but if you could manifest anything you want life would be a boring game.\n\n- Stanley\n|\nHe awoke at six, as usual. He needed no alarm clock. He was already comprehensively alarmed.\n\n- Martin Amis, The Information\n|\nLook at yourself—Are your eyes Twinkling? Is your heart Dancing? Are your lips Smiling? If yes, then you are truly enjoying Life.\n\n- RVM\n|\nLiterature is the human activity that takes the fullest and most 